        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 5:57PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles northwest of Dozier
to 8 miles east of Opp. Movement was southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Andalusia, Opp, Evergreen, Florala, Georgiana, McKenzie, River Falls,
Red Level, Laurel Hill, Lockhart, Dozier, Heath, Gantt, and I65 And
US 84.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
